The paper proposes a learning-based hashing method for efficient retrieval and storage of high-dimensional data such as images and videos. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The method is based on supervised learning and optimization, which suggests machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as other possible categories. The paper also mentions large-scale datasets and classification, which could indicate multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as additional categories.
